headline: VLTO Q3 Deep Dive: Tariff Mitigation, Data Center Growth, and Margin Trends
summary: Water analytics and treatment company Veralto (NYSE:VLTO) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 6.8% year on year to $1.40 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $1.38 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.4% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.99 per share was 4.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
